Ingredients:
- 2 Apples
- 2 tablespoons butter
- 2 teaspoons ground cinnamon
- 2 slices whole wheat toast
- 2 tablespoons honey

Instructions:
1. Preheat oven to 350Â°F.
2. Peel and core the apples, then cut them into 1/2-inch slices.
3. Place the apples in an 8-inch square baking dish and dot with butter.
4. Sprinkle with the cinnamon and drizzle with the honey.
5. Bake in the preheated oven for 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
6. Meanwhile, toast the slices of bread until golden and lightly crisp.
7. Serve the warm apples over the toasted bread slices. Enjoy!
title: Cinnamon Apples and Toast
